ang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"http://www.websitedefender.com/?p=4222";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:378:"The WebsiteDefender team has released a new series of security checks and enhancements which allows the crawler to scan bigger websites, provides additional protection against malware and prevents scanning interruptions in case of any connectivity issue. Enhanced Crawler Module The new crawler module is more efficient and now capable of crawling larger websites. In case [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Adriana Bantu";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2239:"<p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-4226" title="WebsiteDefender Updates January 2012" src="http://www.websitedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/websitedefender-update.gif" alt="WebsiteDefender Improves Malware Detection" width="238" height="110" />The WebsiteDefender team has released a new series of security checks and enhancements which allows the crawler to scan bigger websites, provides additional protection against malware and prevents scanning interruptions in case of any connectivity issue.</p>\n<h2>Enhanced Crawler Module</h2>\n<p>The new crawler module is more efficient and now capable of crawling larger websites. In case of connectivity disruptions, partial scan results are automatically saved and, once the connection is back, the scan will continue without restarting. Further security issues are identified due to a deeper analysis of the website or blog and better link detection.</p>\n<h2>Improved Malware Detection</h2>\n<p>WebsiteDefender checks for more malware:<br />\n1. WebsiteDefender will scan .htaccess file for any malware injected links.<br />\n2. WebsiteDefender will check the configuration files of your website or blog to detect if your website is being redirected automatically to a malware infected site via your Custom Error Responses.</p>\n<h2>Service Quality Improvements</h2>\n<p>We continuously improve our service quality to ensure smooth and efficient scanning. This time we focused on the following features:<br />\n1. TheWebsiteDefender service core is more stable, faster and consumes less bandwidth, meaning that users can benefit from a much higher speed without facing any application inconsistencies.<br />\n2. WebsiteDefender developed a reliable system that assures high-availability service for its users, even during a maintenance period.<br />\n<em><strong></strong></em></p>\n<h4><em><strong>Do you find these updates useful for your website or blog?</strong></em></h4>\n<p>Share your feedback with other users on the <a title="WebsiteDefender''s Facebook page" href="http://www.facebook.com/WebsiteDefender" target="_blank">WebsiteDefender Facebook page</a>, the<a title="WebsiteDefender forum" href="http://www.websitedefender.com/forums/"> forum</a>, or leave a comment.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:114:"http://www.websitedefender.com/announcements/websitedefender-news/websitedefender-improves-malware-detection/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data"